  <img src="C:/Users/USER/.gemini/antigravity/brain/6500ed53-115c-4abd-abcb-3c1580976dd6/conceptual_framework_1783855133730.png" alt="Figure 2.5">
  <div class="figure-caption">Figure 2.5: Conceptual Framework diagram, showing the relationship between independent variables (sensor precision, edge buffering, encryption, version checks), dependent variables (hatchability, zero telemetry loss, data integrity, update awareness), and moderating variables (network reliability, power stability).</div>
</div>

<h4>2.5.2 Explanation of the Diagram</h4>
<p>The framework consists of:</p>
<ul>
  <li><b>Independent Variables (System Inputs)</b>: The design features of the proposed system:
    <ol>
      <li><i>Continuous Temperature & Humidity Sensing</i>: Constant environmental monitoring.</li>
      <li><i>Offline Edge Ring Buffering</i>: Local caching during network drops.</li>
      <li><i>JWT Access Control & MQTTS-TLS Encryption</i>: System security measures.</li>
      <li><i>Automated Edge Version Verification</i>: Firmware lifecycle management.</li>
    </ol>
  </li>
  <li><b>Dependent Variables (System Out-of-the-Box Outcomes)</b>: The target metrics:
    <ol>
      <li><i>Optimized Embryonic Hatchability Rate</i>: Preserving embryonic viability.</li>
      <li><i>Zero Telemetry Log Loss</i>: Complete environmental records.</li>
      <li><i>Telemetry Data Integrity & Operator Trust</i>: Protecting against data tampering.</li>
      <li><i>Operator Update Awareness</i>: Notifying users of security updates.</li>
    </ol>
  </li>
  <li><b>Moderating Variables (Environmental Factors)</b>: Factors that influence system performance:
    <ol>
      <li><i>Local Power Grid Stability</i>: Power availability at the farm.</li>
      <li><i>Rural Wi-Fi Network Reliability</i>: Wireless signal strength.</li>
    </ol>
  </li>
</ul>

