<h3>2.6 Empirical Review</h3>

<h4>2.6.1 Detailed Review of Core Empirical Studies</h4>
<p>The empirical review examines historical deployments of smart incubator and poultry management systems:</p>
<ol>
  <li><b>Protopappas, Bechtsis, & Tsotsolas (2025)</b>: Evaluated IoT architectures for food cold chains. Adopted a cloud-based ingestion backend. Found that real-time monitoring reduced food waste by 22%. <i>Limitation</i>: Did not address edge-node security or update notifications. <i>Relevance</i>: Informs cloud ingestion logic.</li>
  <li><b>Pacheco da Costa et al. (2023)</b>: Reviewed 45 agricultural WSN papers. Identified that 65% of WSN deployments suffered from packet drops. <i>Limitation</i>: Offered no concrete edge buffering algorithm. <i>Relevance</i>: Supports the need for the offline ring buffer.</li>
  <li><b>Nalendra & Waspada (2025)</b>: Implemented WebSockets in a broiler farm app. Achieved latency of under 500ms for UI updates. <i>Limitation</i>: No background execution; alerts silenced when app closed. <i>Relevance</i>: Guides WebSocket integration.</li>
  <li><b>Gatkal et al. (2025)</b>: Conducted a systematic review of WSN topologies in smart farming. <i>Limitation</i>: Lacked implementation details. <i>Relevance</i>: Connects WSN design with smart farming.</li>
  <li><b>TTI Cold Chain Study (2024)</b>: Explored time-temperature data exchanges in food supply chains. <i>Limitation</i>: Evaluated logistics rather than stationary environments. <i>Relevance</i>: Demonstrates the importance of continuous logging.</li>
  <li><b>Terence, Immaculate, Raj, & Nadarajan (2024)</b>: Systematic review of livestock monitoring CPS. <i>Limitation</i>: Conceptual paper without source code validation. <i>Relevance</i>: Supports the cyber-physical system design.</li>
  <li><b>Okello, Ahimbisibwe, & Tukamuhebwa (2025)</b>: Designed an ESP32 Blynk incubator. <i>Limitation</i>: Gaps in data logs during Wi-Fi drops, no security measures. <i>Relevance</i>: Establishes baseline ESP32/Blynk incubator performance.</li>
  <li><b>Abraham Atosona & Stephen (2025)</b>: Simulated a GSM smart incubator. <i>Limitation</i>: High SMS latency, lack of visual interface. <i>Relevance</i>: Supports the move to internet-based protocols.</li>
  <li><b>Abdullah & Hamdan (2023)</b>: Built an MQTT incubator monitor. <i>Limitation</i>: No background alerts, lacked access control. <i>Relevance</i>: Informs MQTT topic structures.</li>
  <li><b>Noor Abdullah Mohammed & Ziad Saeed Mohammed (2025)</b>: Reviewed automated poultry management systems. <i>Limitation</i>: Lacked security analyses. <i>Relevance</i>: Details target environmental thresholds.</li>
  <li><b>Okubanjo (2025)</b>: Proposed a sustainable poultry WSN. <i>Limitation</i>: Conceptual model, did not implement mobile dashboard. <i>Relevance</i>: Focuses on open-source, low-cost microcontrollers.</li>
  <li><b>Trust (2026)</b>: Implemented an ESP32 incubator. <i>Limitation</i>: No transport encryption, did not address firmware updates. <i>Relevance</i>: Guides DS18B20 1-Wire sensor wiring.</li>
  <li><b>Dr. Brindha S et al. (2025)</b>: Used AIoT for poultry monitoring. <i>Limitation</i>: Did not address firmware security updates. <i>Relevance</i>: Supports the integration of push notifications.</li>
  <li><b>K. Ramanan (2025)</b>: Automated temperature regulation in poultry farms. <i>Limitation</i>: High installation cost, restricted adoption. <i>Relevance</i>: Highlights the need for low-cost, open-source solutions.</li>
  <li><b>Sahoo & Pattnaik (2019)</b>: Built an IoT poultry farm. <i>Limitation</i>: No cloud logging, no remote notifications. <i>Relevance</i>: Focuses on localized relay control.</li>
</ol>

<h4>2.6.2 Thematic Summary Matrix</h4>
<p>The comparative matrix (refer to thesis document Section 2.7) lists system stacks, alerting, buffering, and security postures for these 15 key references.</p>

<hr>

<h3>2.7 Research Gap</h3>

<h4>2.7.1 The Isolation of Smart Environmental Architecture from Mobile App Security</h4>
<p>In current agricultural IoT literature, system design and security are treated as separate concerns. Projects focus on temperature precision while leaving data channels unencrypted and access unauthenticated.</p>

<h4>2.7.2 Absence of Low-Cost, Secure Storage Platforms for Developing Agricultural Economies</h4>
<p>There is a lack of end-to-end, secure, open-source systems specifically designed to run on resource-constrained networks. The development of a secure, lightweight, and offline-resilient platform using standard frameworks like FastAPI and Flutter represents a clear contribution to the field.</p>

